==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peele
<hw>Pee"le</hw> <pr>(p⟦emac⟧"l⟦esl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A graceful and swift South African antelope
(<spn>Pelea capreola</spn>). The hair is woolly, and ash-gray on the
back and sides. The horns are black, long, slender, straight, nearly
smooth, and very sharp. Called also <altname>rheeboc</altname>,
<altname>rhebuck</altname>, <altname>rhebok</altname>, and
<altname>rehboc</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>peeled</ent>⟦br⟧
